commit.message:
Add continuous scroll mode for song fields.

The default is now a continuous scroll, instead of the back-and-forth
bounce; this can be changed by setting `mode=b` in the field options.

It is also possible to change the padding from the default `'   '` with
the `padding="..."` option.

Example: `{song format="%(title)s",mode=c,padding=" | "}` will provide a
continuous scroll, separated with ` | `.

Note: Text will be stripped before padding.

Fix line parsing with quote at end of field.

A line with `{song format="%(title)s"}` would crash during parsing.

Fix encoding handling.

- Properly apply chosen charset when sending text to LCDd
- Encode the whole command, not just the text part

Note: I couldn't find an official reference for the LCDd network
encoding. We assume that:
- the encoding chosen by the user in [connections] lcdproc_charset
  is understood by LCDd (notably, encodes lcdproc command characters to
  their ascii code points)
- the actual text decoding is handled by the lcdd driver.

Fix Python3 compatibility.

- Remove iteritems()
- Remove useless double UTF-8 decoding
- Misc typos/import errors.

Add vendored lcdproc library.

Upstream is dead, and doesn't work under Python3.
Linting: Adjust line length, spacing. indent.

Cleanup packaging.

- Single requirements file
- Requirements in setup.py
- Improved Makefile

Merge pull request #19 from jjtt/master

Support for different screen priorities
